132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1271
H.P. 846 House of Representatives, March 25, 2025
An Act to Make Permanent the Law Allowing School Boards to
Accept the Volunteer Services of Immediate Family Members of
Superintendents or School Board Members
Reference to the Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CARLOW of Buxton.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA ยง1002, sub-ยง2-C is enacted to read:
3 2-C. Permissive volunteer placement by school administrative unit.
4 Notwithstanding subsection 2-A, a school board may, but is not required to, permit a
5 superintendent's or school board member's spouse or other family member to serve as a
6 volunteer. A school board may adopt a written policy on nepotism to discourage favoritism
7 and political patronage, consider the needs of the school system and provide that all
8 volunteers have a fair and equal opportunity to be selected on merit, with priority
9 consideration given to the best interest of students without restrictions based solely on
10 family association.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill reestablishes a law that was repealed through a statutory repeal clause in 2024
1133 that allows a school board to permit a spouse of a school board member to serve as a
1144 volunteer. This bill expands the law that was repealed in 2024 to include a superintendent's
1155 or school board member's spouse or other family members.
